---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  lang="en"
  active="privacy"
  title="Privacy Policy | Food Label Detective"
  description="Privacy policy for Food Label Detective, including camera, gallery, OCR, internet, database synchronization, data retention, and security use."
  alternateUrl="/app/tr/privacy-policy/"
>
  <main class="site-shell policy-hero policy-content">
    <span class="eyebrow">Privacy Policy</span>
    <h1>We read the label text, not your private life.</h1>
    <p class="lede">This policy explains what permissions Food Label Detective uses, what data is processed, and how the app protects user privacy.</p>
    <p class="notice"><strong>Last updated:</strong> June 12, 2026. The app is provided for general information only and does not make medical, legal, halal certification, or official regulatory decisions.</p>

    <h2>1. App information</h2>
    <p><strong>App name:</strong> Food Label Detective</p>
    <p><strong>Developer:</strong> Mehmet Büküm</p>
    <p><strong>Contact:</strong> <a href="mailto:mehmetbkm@gmail.com">mehmetbkm@gmail.com</a></p>

    <h2>2. Information processed</h2>
    <p>Food Label Detective helps detect E-codes and additive names on food labels. Label images captured with the camera or selected from the gallery are used only for on-device OCR processing.</p>
    <p>The app does not require user registration or login.</p>

    <h2>3. Camera and gallery use</h2>
    <p>Camera permission is used to capture food labels and read text through OCR. Gallery images are processed for the same purpose.</p>
    <p>Label images are not uploaded to a remote server by the app, are not stored by us, and are not shared with third parties.</p>

    <h2>4. On-device OCR technology</h2>
    <p>The app may use on-device text recognition technology to read label text. OCR processing is performed on the user's device. Label images are not sent to an external OCR server by the app.</p>
    <p>OCR accuracy may vary depending on lighting, blur, angle, package reflections, and label quality.</p>

    <h2>5. Internet access</h2>
    <p>Internet access is used to update the additive database, reach the live data source, and check connection status.</p>
    <p>The app may communicate with its own API service to synchronize additive database records. The app can continue basic searches with the local database stored on the device.</p>

    <h2>6. Additive data</h2>
    <p>The app may display additive code, name, purpose, halal status, health note, risk level, description, warning, and alias fields.</p>
    <p>This information is for general guidance only.</p>

    <h2>7. Sharing and third parties</h2>
    <p>The app does not upload label photos or OCR images to a server for sharing with third parties.</p>
    <p>The app does not sell personal user data.</p>
    <p>The app may use third-party libraries or Android services required for app functionality, such as on-device text recognition. These are used only to provide the app's label-reading and search features.</p>

    <h2>8. Data retention and deletion</h2>
    <p>Food Label Detective does not create user accounts and does not store label photos, gallery images, or OCR image files on its servers.</p>
    <p>Additive database records may be stored locally on the user's device to allow offline or local searches. Users can remove locally stored app data by clearing the app data or uninstalling the app from their device.</p>
    <p>For privacy-related questions or deletion requests, users can contact <a href="mailto:mehmetbkm@gmail.com">mehmetbkm@gmail.com</a>.</p>

    <h2>9. Security</h2>
    <p>When the app communicates with its API service to synchronize additive records, the connection is made through secure HTTPS where supported.</p>
    <p>The app does not transmit label photos or OCR images to the API service.</p>

    <h2>10. Children’s privacy</h2>
    <p>The app is not directed to children and is not designed to collect personal data from children. Additive information is presented as general educational guidance.</p>

    <h2>11. User responsibility</h2>
    <p>OCR can make mistakes. Before making a final decision, users should check the product package, manufacturer statements, official regulations, certification bodies, and qualified expert guidance.</p>

    <h2>12. Disclaimer</h2>
    <p>Food Label Detective is an independent information tool built to make food labels easier to understand.</p>
    <p>The information provided in the app does not replace product labels, manufacturer statements, official certifications, medical advice, legal advice, or professional guidance.</p>

    <h2>13. Contact</h2>
    <p>For privacy questions or correction requests, contact <a href="mailto:mehmetbkm@gmail.com">mehmetbkm@gmail.com</a>.</p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
